<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2026 01:24:13 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>谁的意识？</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/whose-consciousness-would-it-be</link><description>采样和缩放可以告诉我们关于有意识的人工智能的信息。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/whose-consciousness-would-it-be2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 13:13:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/whose-consciousness-would-it-be</guid></item><item><title>从细胞到恒星再到粒子的一切都存在于混沌的边缘</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/everything-from-cells-to-stars-to-particles-exists-on-the-edge-of-chaos</link><description>复杂的系统，无论是生物体还是基本粒子，都需要有足够的结构来结合在一起，并且具有允许变化的不可预测性。专栏作家托马斯·卢顿探讨了这个想法是否只是宇宙中可见的一种模式，或者可能是一种“万有理论” &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/everything-from-cells-to-stars-to-particles-exists-on-the-edge-of-chaos.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 12:58:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/everything-from-cells-to-stars-to-particles-exists-on-the-edge-of-chaos</guid></item><item><title>您的代理没有内存问题</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/your-agent-doesnt-have-a-memory-problem</link><description>每个人都在竞相为特工提供记忆。真正破坏他们的失败存在于其他地方。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/your-agent-doesnt-have-a-memory-problem2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 12:43:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/your-agent-doesnt-have-a-memory-problem</guid></item><item><title>这种胶水可粘合到不粘表面并用乙醇擦拭干净</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/this-glue-bonds-to-nonstick-surfaces-and-wipes-clean-with-ethanol</link><description>外部专家表示，应研究氟化分子对环境的影响&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/this-glue-bonds-to-nonstick-surfaces-and-wipes-clean-with-ethanol.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 12:28:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/this-glue-bonds-to-nonstick-surfaces-and-wipes-clean-with-ethanol</guid></item><item><title>奇怪的粒子可能是现实中缺失的成分</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/strange-paraparticles-could-be-realitys-missing-ingredient</link><description>无论是物质还是力，超粒子都将是完全不同的东西。它们存在的新迹象让人们燃起了希望，希望它们能够在最深层次上解释现实&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/strange-paraparticles-could-be-realitys-missing-ingredient.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 12:13:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/strange-paraparticles-could-be-realitys-missing-ingredient</guid></item><item><title>物理学家弗兰克·威尔切克对现实本质的独特见解</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/physicist-frank-wilczeks-unique-insights-on-the-nature-of-reality</link><description>弗兰克·威尔切克 (Frank Wilczek) 是理论物理学领域最杰出、最具独创性的人之一，他提出了时间晶体的想法。他的好奇心现在带他去哪里？ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/physicist-frank-wilczeks-unique-insights-on-the-nature-of-reality.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 11:58:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/physicist-frank-wilczeks-unique-insights-on-the-nature-of-reality</guid></item><item><title>一个简单的物理实验如何揭示隐藏在额外维度中的暗物质</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/how-a-simple-physics-experiment-could-reveal-dark-matter-hiding-in-an-extra-dimension</link><description>宇宙失踪的物质是否隐藏在“黑暗”的额外维度中？我们现在有简单的方法来测试这个奇怪的想法——以及更普遍的额外维度的存在&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-a-simple-physics-experiment-could-reveal-dark-matter-hiding-in-an-extra-dimension.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 11:43:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/how-a-simple-physics-experiment-could-reveal-dark-matter-hiding-in-an-extra-dimension</guid></item><item><title>AI代理帮助准备同步加速器X射线实验测量，为自主操作铺平道路</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/ai-agent-helps-prepare-synchrotron-x-ray-experimental-measurements-paving-the-way-for-autonomous-operation</link><description>如今，全世界许多人每天都在使用人工智能 (AI) 模型，无论是出于专业目的还是个人目的。在过去的几十年里，各个学科的科学家也开始使用这些模型来进行研究或简化他们的实验实践。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ai-agent-helps-prepare-synchrotron-x-ray-experimental-measurements-paving-the-way-for-autonomous-operation2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 11:28:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/ai-agent-helps-prepare-synchrotron-x-ray-experimental-measurements-paving-the-way-for-autonomous-operation</guid></item><item><title>微软希望通过将 GPT 和 Claude 换成中国的 Kimi K3 担任副驾驶，从而节省多达 6 亿美元，冒着特朗普政府的责骂</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/microsoft-looking-to-save-as-much-as-600-million-by-swapping-gpt-and-claude-for-chinas-kimi-k3-in-copilot-risking-a-rap-on-the-knuckles-from-the-trump-administration</link><description>微软正在将 Kimi K3 添加到其 Azure 云服务中，同时其工程师继续评估该模型以在 Copilot 中部署。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/microsoft-looking-to-save-as-much-as-600-million-by-swapping-gpt-and-claude-for-chinas-kimi-k3-in-copilot-risking-a-rap-on-the-knuckles-from-the-trump-administration2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 11:13:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/microsoft-looking-to-save-as-much-as-600-million-by-swapping-gpt-and-claude-for-chinas-kimi-k3-in-copilot-risking-a-rap-on-the-knuckles-from-the-trump-administration</guid></item><item><title>用于新物理研究的降噪分子</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/noise-proofing-molecules-for-new-physics-searches</link><description>某些分子可以处于对外部噪音不太敏感的状态，为研究人员提供一个安静的系统来探测基础物理。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/noise-proofing-molecules-for-new-physics-searches2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 10:58:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/07/noise-proofing-molecules-for-new-physics-searches</guid></item></channel></rss>